This paper is about improving the decoding speed of Neural Machine Translation (NMT) using a more flexible beam search strategy. NMT is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP) which falls under the Computer Science category. Specifically, the paper deals with improving the performance of the decoder, which involves optimizing the search algorithm used to generate translations. This falls under the sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG, cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for image captioning, which falls under the sub-category of Computer Vision (cs.CV).
